== Scratchbox 2 With Maemo ==

These instructions work for Maemo SDK 3.1 release.

=== Step by Step Guide for Debian/testing and Debian/unstable Hosts ===
{{{
$ sudo apt-get install scratchbox2 qemu
}}}
Download CodeSourcery [http://www.codesourcery.com/gnu_toolchains/arm/download.html toolchain]. Select
"ARM GNU/Linux" for Target Platform, and "IA32 GNU/Linux" for Host Platform. Save the file to your
$HOME directory.
{{{
$ cd $HOME
$ tar jxf arm-2007q3-51-arm-none-linux-gnueabi-i686-pc-linux-gnu.tar.bz2
$ cd arm-2007q3/bin
$ ln -s arm-none-linux-gnueabi-gcc arm-none-linux-gnueabi-cc
$ for f in *; do ln -s $f $(echo $f | sed 's/arm-none-linux-gnueabi-/arm-linux-/'); done
$ mkdir $HOME/buildroot
$ cd $HOME/buildroot
$ wget http://repository.maemo.org/stable/3.1/armel/maemo-sdk-rootstrap_3.1_armel.tgz
$ tar zxf maemo-sdk-rootstrap_3.1_armel.tgz
$ sb2-init -m maemo maemo $HOME/arm-2007q3/bin/arm-linux-gcc
}}}

=== Partial Step by Step Guide for non-Debian i386 Hosts ===

First you need to get a decently functioning qemu for your system, it must have -drop-ld-preload supported. You will also need gnu make 3.81 or newer to build scratchbox2.

Second important thing is to install a debian/etch system somewhere on your host using debootstrap. It will be used as the
build tools. We'll assume you've put it into /etch_root. You need to install all those tools into it that you need
for building your software.
{{{
$ wget http://people.freedesktop.org/~lle/sbox2-releases/sbox2-1.99.0.20.tar.bz2
$ tar jxf sbox2-1.99.0.20.tar.bz2
$ cd sbox2-1.99.0.20
$ ./autogen.sh
$ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/scratchbox2
$ make
$ make install
}}}
The steps below are almost identical to those given for Debian systems.
{{{
$ cd $HOME
$ tar jxf arm-2007q3-51-arm-none-linux-gnueabi-i686-pc-linux-gnu.tar.bz2
$ cd arm-2007q3/bin
$ ln -s arm-none-linux-gnueabi-gcc arm-none-linux-gnueabi-cc
$ for f in *; do ln -s $f $(echo $f | sed 's/arm-none-linux-gnueabi-/arm-linux-/'); done
$ mkdir $HOME/buildroot
$ cd $HOME/buildroot
$ wget http://repository.maemo.org/stable/3.1/armel/maemo-sdk-rootstrap_3.1_armel.tgz
$ tar zxf maemo-sdk-rootstrap_3.1_armel.tgz
$ $HOME/scratchbox2/bin/sb2-init -m maemo maemo -t /etch_root $HOME/arm-2007q3/bin/arm-linux-gcc
}}}

Add $HOME/scratchbox2/bin to your PATH.

== Functionality Verification ==

After completing either one of the above step-by-step guides, you should verify with a simple hello-world style program that everything is working. Put this into hello.c:
{{{
#include <stdio.h>
int main(int argc, char **argv)
{
    printf("Hello, World!\n");
}
}}}

Compile it with:
{{{
$ sb2 gcc -o hello hello.c
}}}

Run it with:
{{{
$ sb2 ./hello
}}}

